# Copy this file to authorized_keys (gitignored) and put your SSH public key(s)
# here, one bare OpenSSH public key per line, then pass
# --authorized-keys-file ./authorized_keys when creating or spawning the VM.
#
# SSH is only needed to log in after boot (e.g. to run `hermes setup --portal`
# or tail logs); the macOS app itself connects over port 9119, not SSH.
#
# ssh-ed25519 AAAA... you@your-mac
